# Maze Engineers — Research Trend Forecaster

A standalone, self-contained HTML dashboard for tracking PubMed publication trends, forecasting product demand, and receiving real-time alerts when new high-impact papers are published — across Maze Engineers' full behavioral neuroscience equipment catalogue.

---

## Overview

The Research Trend Forecaster gives the Maze Engineers team instant access to publication volume trends, AI-generated demand forecasts, recent high-impact journal publications, and automated new publication alerts — all organized by product category and species. No external API keys or backend required. All trend and forecast data is pre-baked into the file; live PubMed scanning runs directly from the browser.

---

## Features

### Trend & Forecast View
- Annual publication counts (2020–2024) sourced from PubMed, displayed as a bar chart
- Four key stats per product: 2024 paper count, 5-year growth %, year-over-year change, peak year
- AI-generated demand forecast for 2025 (High / Moderate / Low)
- Confidence score (50–99%)
- Trend classification: Rising, Stable, Declining, or Emerging
- 3 key research drivers specific to each product
- Strategic recommendation for Maze Engineers
- 3 hot research areas

### Publications View
- Up to 8 recent high-impact papers (2024–2025) per product
- Sorted by journal impact factor (highest first)
- Color-coded impact tier:
  - 🟣 Purple — IF 20+ (top tier: Nature, Cell, Science)
  - 🟢 Green — IF 10–20 (high impact)
  - 🟡 Yellow — IF 5–10 (solid journals)
  - Gray — IF below 5 or unknown
- Each paper includes: title (linked to PubMed/DOI), journal, authors, date, impact factor bar
- NEW 2025 badge for papers published this year
- Live "Search latest papers on PubMed" button for every product — always up to date

### 🔔 Publication Alerts (New in v1.1)
- One-click scan across **all 75+ products simultaneously** — no manual checking required
- Configurable date range: last 30 / 60 / 90 days / 6 months / 12 months
- Configurable minimum impact factor threshold: IF 3+ / 5+ / 10+ / 20+
- Live progress bar showing scan status per product
- Summary stats: total papers found, products with new papers, high-impact count
- Results sorted by journal impact factor — highest first
- Red dot indicator on the alert button when high-impact papers (IF 10+) are found
- 150+ journal impact factors pre-loaded for instant IF lookup
- Links directly to PubMed or DOI for every paper
- Powered by NCBI PubMed E-utilities API (free, no key required)

