## Updating the Pre-Baked Data

All trend data, forecasts, and featured publications are stored in the `DATA` object inside the `<script>` tag. Each product entry contains:

```js
'Product Name': {
  c: [2020_count, 2021_count, 2022_count, 2023_count, 2024_count],
  t: 'Rising',           // trend label: Rising | Stable | Declining | Emerging
  cf: 88,                // confidence score (50–99)
  d: 'High',             // demand forecast: High | Moderate | Low
  dr: ['driver 1', 'driver 2', 'driver 3'],
  r: 'Recommendation text for Maze Engineers.',
  a: ['hot area 1', 'hot area 2', 'hot area 3'],
  p: [                   // featured publications (sorted by IF descending)
    {
      ti: 'Paper title',
      au: 'Authors et al.',
      j:  'Journal Name',
      y:  '2024',
      m:  'Jan',
      pm: 'PMID',        // PubMed ID (or null)
      doi: '10.xxx/yyy', // DOI (or null)
      if: 6.5,           // impact factor (or null)
      n:  false          // true = NEW 2025
    }
  ]
}
```

To add a journal to the impact factor lookup table, find the `JIF` object in the script and add an entry:
```js
'Journal of Example Science': 8.4,
```

